# Supabase direct or session-pooler connection (not transaction pooler — EF migrations on startup).
# Paste the full URI from Supabase Dashboard → Connect, or use key=value format.
#
# Session pooler (recommended for dev):
# SITE_ANALYZER2_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.<project-ref>:<password>@aws-1-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
#
# Direct:
# SITE_ANALYZER2_DATABASE_URL=Host=db.<project-ref>.supabase.co;Port=5432;Database=postgres;Username=postgres;Password=<password>;SSL Mode=Require;Trust Server Certificate=true
#
# Business focus (required): openai | anthropic | human
# BUSINESS_FOCUS_PROVIDER=human
#
# CORS (required): comma-separated browser origins allowed to call the Api
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000
#
# Web import resolves Geek-SEO project id from site_profiles (no operator .env).
# First import on a new site URL: set GEEK_SEO_PROJECT_ID on this Api service (Railway).
# GEEK_SEO_PROJECT_ID=
# Local Docker Postgres (docker compose up -d) — use key=value, not postgresql:// URI:
# SITE_ANALYZER2_DATABASE_URL=Host=localhost;Port=5432;Database=siteanalyzer2;Username=postgres;Password=postgres
#
# See docs/LOCAL-DEV.md for the full local setup guide.
